{
  "texts": [
    "This model takes into account not only the dissociation of quarkonium, but also the possibility of recombination of Q Q into secondary quarkonium states [197,198].",
    "We recall two basic features of the comover approach.",
    "First, larger quarkonia are more affected by dissociation, due to larger interaction cross sections.",
    "As a consequence, excited states are more suppressed than the ground states.",
    "Second, the suppression increases with comover densities, which are proportional to particle multiplicities."
  ]
}